just like my syrup can.

14:02.108 --> 14:05.476
I can open my own case,
thank you.

14:05.611 --> 14:08.012
Fonzie, aren't you gonna do
anything about those two?

14:08.147 --> 14:10.173
Hey, my beautiful Blossom,

14:10.316 --> 14:13.877
the Fonz does not meddle
in the battle of the sexes, huh?

14:14.020 --> 14:16.785
Come on. Let's go out there and
shake hands with Mother Nature.

14:16.923 --> 14:18.891
How about we take a,
a beautiful long walk

14:19.025 --> 14:20.049
through the woods, huh?

14:20.193 --> 14:22.923
- Just you and me, huh?
-(Blossom clears throat)

14:23.062 --> 14:25.224
Are there any wild animals
out there?

14:25.364 --> 14:27.162
No. Well, just one.

14:27.300 --> 14:31.259
It's wearing
a long, red plaid scarf.

14:31.404 --> 14:33.634
Whoa!

14:34.807 --> 14:36.002
(wind whistling)

14:36.142 --> 14:38.577
Come on, guys, let's get started
setting up, okay?

14:38.711 --> 14:40.042
- All right, yeah, yeah.
- Sure, sure.

14:40.179 --> 14:42.239
- Hey, Leather.
- Hi, Leather. -Hey, Leather.

14:42.381 --> 14:45.146
- Hey, guys.
- Gotcha!

14:45.284 --> 14:46.616
- Hey, you made it.
- Yeah. -Yeah.

14:46.753 --> 14:47.742
Yeah, for a while there,

14:47.887 --> 14:49.184
I thought you got lost
or something.

14:49.322 --> 14:51.222
Well, we would have made it
soonen

14:51.357 --> 14:53.451
-but the huskies couldn't pull
the car. -(all laugh)

14:53.593 --> 14:54.890
Humor for all seasons.

14:55.027 --> 14:57.258
Yeah, I know, I know it's
a little bit out of the way,

14:57.396 --> 14:59.422
but I'm doing it as a favor
for an old friend.

14:59.565 --> 15:02.501
Oh, yeah? Who's your friend,
Smokey the Bear? Another one!

15:02.635 --> 15:03.898
I'm hot tonight.

15:04.036 --> 15:05.163
No, it's Ma Hopkins.

15:05.304 --> 15:07.500
She used to be in reform school
with me, as a cook.

15:07.640 --> 15:09.506
And now she's making
a go of this place.

15:09.642 --> 15:10.734
RALPH:
Oh, yeah?

15:10.877 --> 15:11.969
Hey, where are the Suedes?

15:12.111 --> 15:13.238
- What, Millie and Tillie?
- Yeah.

15:13.379 --> 15:14.744
They're in the kitchen
making chili.

15:14.881 --> 15:16.280
- Beat ya!
- You did, you did.

15:16.415 --> 15:17.610
(triangle rings)

15:17.750 --> 15:19.445
Oh, that's her.
Dinner's ready.

15:19.585 --> 15:20.985
Come on. I'll show you
where to put your things,

15:21.120 --> 15:23.783
and then we can get
a bite to eat.

15:23.923 --> 15:25.322
BOTH:
I'm not hungry.

15:25.458 --> 15:26.948
I am. I love chili.

15:27.093 --> 15:28.083
Hey, Malph, free food.

15:29.962 --> 15:31.931
(grunts)

15:32.064 --> 15:33.396
Are you all right?

15:33.533 --> 15:36.468
Ah, just a splinter,
little lady.

15:36.602 --> 15:38.969
Aw. Here, here, don't do that!

15:39.105 --> 15:42.097
I'll pull it out.
I have long nails.

15:42.241 --> 15:44.676
Wait a minute.
Lori Beth, long nails?

15:44.811 --> 15:46.210
I don't think...

15:46.345 --> 15:51.374
Look... do you really have
to do this?

15:51.517 --> 15:52.917
Ah. Thanks. That feels better.

15:53.052 --> 15:55.885
We'll go to the kitchen.
I'll wash it off.

15:57.290 --> 16:00.487
We're going to the kitchen
to wash my hands.

16:00.626 --> 16:04.427
Who do you think you are,
Florence Nightingale?

