21:42.902 --> 21:44.961
- Isn't it beautiful?
- Oh, yeah.

21:45.104 --> 21:47.436
I'll tell you something,
I'll bet you've looked at those

21:47.573 --> 21:50.372
all your life, but you never
really saw it like this, huh?

21:50.509 --> 21:52.569
I mean, just look
at the colors- the ice blue,

21:52.711 --> 21:54.771
the white and everything.
Why don't you take it

21:54.914 --> 21:57.280
over to the fire there
and watch it melt?

21:57.416 --> 21:59.441
Yeah, then we'll
put it all back together.

21:59.585 --> 22:00.882
Yeah, whatever you say.

22:04.590 --> 22:05.853
Okay.

22:05.991 --> 22:08.517
Why'd you jump on his back?
He's a mountain.

22:08.661 --> 22:09.958
Well, it was just embarrassing.

22:10.095 --> 22:11.859
The man hung me in a tree.

22:11.997 --> 22:13.693
Well, he took you down.

22:13.832 --> 22:15.960
Are you siding with him, Lori
Beth? Are you starting again?

22:16.101 --> 22:18.070
- Are you gonna side with...?
- All right, hold it, hold it,

22:18.204 --> 22:19.193
hold it!

22:19.338 --> 22:22.000
I am tired of listening
to you two bicker.

22:22.141 --> 22:23.665
You know what I mean?
Now, you...

22:23.809 --> 22:25.334
right here, you got to choose

22:25.477 --> 22:27.139
who you're
gonna be friendly with,

22:27.279 --> 22:30.146
'cause not every guy
is a gentleman like me.

22:30.282 --> 22:32.751
And, you, you got
to let her have some friends

22:32.885 --> 22:35.354
of the opposite gender,
you know? That's only polite.

22:35.487 --> 22:37.888
You know what I mean?
All right, now it's settled.

22:38.023 --> 22:39.650
So kiss and make up.

22:40.826 --> 22:42.157
Pucker up.

22:47.333 --> 22:49.233
Now, don't that feel
much better?

22:49.368 --> 22:52.338
We're gonna go over to the,
uh, fire and finish making up.

22:52.471 --> 22:54.371
- Hey, I think that's
a great idea. -Come on.

22:54.506 --> 22:56.498
FONZIE:
All right.

22:59.511 --> 23:00.911
That was beautiful, Fonzie.

23:01.046 --> 23:02.537
